[SPEAKER_03]: Some of it's in the general fund, some of it is capital expenditures.

610
00:46:08,484 --> 00:46:15,710
[SPEAKER_03]: So if you could give me an estimate, what is our total spending this year on street and sidewalk repair and maintenance?

611
00:46:17,122 --> 00:46:20,625
[SPEAKER_26]: I would have to compile that number because it comes from multiple different sources.

612
00:46:20,886 --> 00:46:21,386
[SPEAKER_26]: Okay.

613
00:46:21,827 --> 00:46:23,308
[SPEAKER_26]: We have our ordinary expenses.

614
00:46:23,568 --> 00:46:30,094
[SPEAKER_26]: So, each year we have money that you know identified lines for things like asphalt, things like concrete.

615
00:46:30,394 --> 00:46:30,754
[SPEAKER_26]: Yeah.

616
00:46:30,915 --> 00:46:39,102
[SPEAKER_26]: So, for the work that we do in house the highway does a very good job of doing that work, but then, you know, we also, we have

617
00:46:39,572 --> 00:46:44,633
[SPEAKER_26]: capital funding that, and we have state aid funding, and then we have loan funding.

618
00:46:44,733 --> 00:46:48,173
[SPEAKER_26]: So it would have to be an exercise where I compile all of that.

619
00:46:48,313 --> 00:46:50,394
[SPEAKER_26]: So I don't want to compile it.

620
00:46:50,534 --> 00:46:52,034
[SPEAKER_03]: If you could, no rush on it.

621
00:46:52,954 --> 00:46:53,214
[SPEAKER_03]: Sure.

622
00:46:53,394 --> 00:46:56,295
[SPEAKER_03]: And then maybe we could do it on an annual basis when you present the budget.

623
00:46:56,315 --> 00:47:03,556
[SPEAKER_03]: Cause I think that would be really helpful for me to say, Oh, you know, cause I saw a few hundred thousand in here in ordinary, I would say maybe 500,000, maybe 600.

624
00:47:04,416 --> 00:47:09,017
[SPEAKER_03]: And then I know we did some bonding and I know chapter 90, hopefully will be going up this year.

625
00:47:10,086 --> 00:47:19,475
[SPEAKER_03]: Um, if we had that total number, then I could say, could be able to compare that to that payment asset management reports and say, oh, so we are doing two and a half million.

626
00:47:19,495 --> 00:47:21,037
[SPEAKER_03]: It said we need three for this.

627
00:47:21,097 --> 00:47:23,499
[SPEAKER_03]: It says we need 10 to really start hitting the backlog.

628
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:27,083
[SPEAKER_03]: Just being able to assess how, how close, how much are we.

629
00:47:28,175 --> 00:47:30,717
[SPEAKER_03]: increasing our spend on street and sidewalk repair every year?

630
00:47:30,737 --> 00:47:30,998
[SPEAKER_26]: Sure.

631
00:47:31,078 --> 00:47:38,024
[SPEAKER_26]: Something more than, you know, I think typically we talk about bigger numbers, but you want something a little bit more detailed from an annual perspective.

632
00:47:38,304 --> 00:47:38,524
[SPEAKER_26]: Yeah.

633
00:47:38,564 --> 00:47:44,789
[SPEAKER_26]: I think, you know, we're doing that, we're tracking that in-house anyway, so I could just compile the numbers and see what we can do for providing that information.

634
00:47:44,809 --> 00:47:45,010
[SPEAKER_26]: Great.

635
00:47:45,130 --> 00:47:47,392
[SPEAKER_26]: But you wanted pavement and sidewalks?

636
00:47:47,892 --> 00:48:03,651
[SPEAKER_03]: And you can do one you know you could do payment and sidewalks and then the total you know you can separate them out whatever is easier but you know, I think the payment report is talking about something in the $10 million range as one of the to really start bringing down the backlog so for spending 2 million.

637
00:48:04,636 --> 00:48:12,141
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, I just want to be able to, if you could base it on what the payment report was saying and the sidewalk report was saying, that would probably be the best thing.

638
00:48:12,161 --> 00:48:12,661
[SPEAKER_26]: Yeah.

639
00:48:13,502 --> 00:48:18,185
[SPEAKER_26]: And in that report too, if I recall, there is some breakdown of what existing expenditures have been.

640
00:48:18,205 --> 00:48:18,866
[SPEAKER_26]: Yeah.

641
00:48:18,946 --> 00:48:19,226
[SPEAKER_26]: Yeah.

642
00:48:19,326 --> 00:48:29,413
[SPEAKER_26]: And it kind of paints that picture in that report to give an idea of what sort of capital investments the city would need to see over the coming years.

643
